<item>
            <title>[LU-4736] sanity-lfsck test_18c: MDS1 is not the expected &apos;completed&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4736</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/602974fa-a5f9-11e3-8a1b-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/602974fa-a5f9-11e3-8a1b-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_18c failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(2) MDS1 is not the expected &apos;completed&apos;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Two instances of this failure seen in the last day, none before that.&lt;br/&gt;
Occurrences don&apos;t look to have anything to do with patches under test.&lt;br/&gt;
I suspect something bad has just landed in master that causes this failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity-lfsck 18c&lt;/p&gt;</description>
