                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="81540" author="jamesanunez" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2014 16:13:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I hit this error recently at &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0d6a1964-c290-11e3-a886-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0d6a1964-c290-11e3-a886-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt; with a build, #22955, from April 9. Build 22955 should have the patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/9661/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/9661/&lt;/a&gt; included. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="81129" author="yong.fan" created="Mon, 7 Apr 2014 17:30:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch has been landed to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="79410" author="yong.fan" created="Sun, 16 Mar 2014 03:31:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is because the LFSCK slave on OST returns -ENODEV (-19) to the LFSCK master on MDT to indicate that related target device does not involve in LFSCK or have finished and left the LFSCK, but such errno has been explained as system recovery by ptlrpc by wrong. I have made a patch to fix it in &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/9661/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/9661/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="79348" author="adilger" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2014 17:20:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It might just be that this test has become slower than before, or is slowed by running in a VM with other systems?  I&apos;m not a big fan of tests that have a specific time to complete, especially after mounting the system (which may take a variable amount of time).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
